content:
Rank the products from the most expensive to the least expensive based on the given prices. However, the prices are stored in a JSON data format. Here is the JSON file that contains the prices of each product:
{
  "products": [
    {
      "name": "Cable TV",
      "price": 49.95
    },
    {
      "name": "Cable Modem",
      "price": 25.49
    },
    {
      "name": "HDMI Cable",
      "price": 17.99
    }
  ]
}
Can you write a Python code that reads the JSON file and ranks the products based on their prices?
